Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat until hot. Brown beef in batches; pour off drippings. Return beef to pan. Stir in salsa, sugar, soy sauce and garlic; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover tightly and simmer 1-3/4 to 2-1/4 hours or until beef is fork-tender. Stir in cilantro and lime juice. Serve over rice.